\is1 Introduction
\ip This is \bk the second letter of Paul that we have that's written to Timothy\bk*. He wrote it from Rome when he was imprisoned there as a result of his preaching about Jesus the messiah. Paul requests Timothy egpeendiyeen of kandin of not pad sikandin eggimatayan. Ne si Timothy, there pad sikandin of Ephesus the egpanulu of believers.
\ip Kayi of this letter, advised of Paul si Timothy eglig‑en so that egpakaantus sikandin egwali and eggimu of impeyimu of God kandin minsan taliware of me peg-antus and me pegsupak of duma person. Impanpanayan din again si Timothy concerning the bad egkeyingumaan of “keungelan and of ware karuan apulanan” su egpakareet this of people egpammineg.
\ip Labew of all, impasuman-suman of Paul si Timothy about his life su so that to become parable of Timothy the faith of Paul, the pegpariralem din, the loving rin, the pegpabulus din, and the peg-antus din taliware of me pegbayad-bayad kandin.
