\c 2
\s1 The good soldier of the messiah Jesus
\p
\v 1 So my ‘son’, may the grace from Jesus the messiah make you strong
\v 2 along with everything you heard from me through many witnesses. Entrust those things to faithful people who will also be capable of teaching others.
\p
\v 3 Suffer together \add with me\add* as a good soldier of Jesus the messiah.
\v 4 Soldiers stay unentangled from the affairs of daily living so that they will \add be dedicated to\add* pleasing their commanding officer.
\v 5 Similarly \add the athlete\add* won't win the competition if they don't follow the rules.
\v 6 It's fair for the farmer working \add in the orchard\add* to be allowed to eat the fruit.
\v 7 You should easily understand what I'm saying because the master will be giving you insight into everything.
\p
\v 8 Always remember the \add promised\add* descendant of King David, Jesus the messiah who came back from the dead, which is what I preach
\v 9 and why here I'm in chains suffering hardship as a criminal. But God's message hasn't been chained.
\v 10 So I will endure everything so that the ones that \add God has\add* chosen will also be able to receive their salvation in Jesus the messiah
